 -----------------------------

 - an error fixed, which caused some Chip memory to be lost
 - linking of BitMapExtension blocks fixed
 - handling of IDCMP_INACTIVEWINDOW fixed (no more trouble with keyboard shortcuts :)
 - verify routine improved


  Version 1.4   18 April 1996
 -----------------------------

 - FileSystem format option added


  Version 1.6     17 May 1996
 -----------------------------

 - detects & utilizes Kickstart 3.0


  Version 1.7     6 July 1996
 -----------------------------

 - timer added
 - `CHIP buffer' option added


  Version 1.8     29 Sep 1996
 -----------------------------

 - an ancient bug in formatting routine fixed
 - better (?) menu layout


  Version 1.86    20 Dec 1997
 -----------------------------

 - some changes in GUI
 - a (harmless) bug fixed in IDCMP handling (another one!)
 - some more tiny optimizations in formatting routine
 - BitMapExtension creating revised
 - WorseFormat now remembers window positions
 - the requesters now adapt to reqtools preferences


  Version 2.0     23 Sep 1998
 -----------------------------

 - lots of small bugfixes and minor improvements
 - the hashing algorithm finally fixed (an international version has been implemented as well)
 - configuration system added
 - 'create icons' option added
 - new hide method: iconification
 - 'Read drive geometry' option added
 - AmigaGuide on-line help implemented
 - the 'Buffers in CHIP-Ram' option removed - now WorseFormat is able to get this information from DOS structures
 - revised guide file (it's still far from perfect though :(
 - Installer script included
 - NewIcons by Philip Vedovatti included


  Version 2.1     29 Oct 1998
 -----------------------------

 - major bug fixed: WF could crash when started from Workbench
 - major bug fixed: WF could create invalid BitMapExtension blocks for very large disks
 - now WF sets the BitMapFlag to 'invalid', letting the Disk-Validator calculate
   the BitMap data. This behaviour doesn't cause any ill effects, and problems with bitmaps
   of very large disks should finally be fixed
 - formatting routine improved
 - a potential Enforcer hit removed (routine which creates the Trashcan icon)
 - two silly bugs in GUI fixed

@endnode

